Tutorial 2:

Enable ssh for bveeta mini:
Some version of bveeta mini doesnt come with preenable ssh. User need to enable by themselves. Below is the steps should follow:

In the terminal type:

sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config

then enable this line below by delete the # sign

PubkeyAuthetication no

save the code by pressing ctrl+o
exit code by pressing ctrl+x

reenable netplan by typing

sudo netplan apply

now you can control bveeta mini through ssh.

good luck.
